body.text: This library allows to build classic racing board game. In this game, the piece move from the lower left tile to the upper tile from left to right. Shortcuts and detours can be added to make the path less obvious.
This library works with the 'board game' library which needs to be initialized first.
You can add shortcuts where the player races ahead on particular tiles. Give the start 'row, column' and end 'row, column' pairs.
You can also add detours where the player goes back in the race.
Pieces can be positioned on the start tile  using 'move piece start'.
To move pieces, specify the number of moves. The library takes care of the shortcuts and detours.
Adds a chute or ladder to the board
Moves a piece a number of moves.
Moves a piece on the first tile of the game (lower left)
Sets the sounds needed when moving a piece
